- v1.0.6 | Apr 11 2026:

  [Change] files/elog_lib.sh: replaced 44-line ELOG_* configuration variable
      prose catalogue at file header with a 3-line cross-reference to
      README.md § 3. Configuration (single source of truth for defaults)
  [Change] files/elog_lib.sh: removed 26 banner separator lines (# ----- style).
      Load-bearing SIEM/CEF/GELF/ECS/API-contract documentation preserved on
      all 8 function/section headers
  [Change] ELOG_LIB_VERSION: 1.0.5 → 1.0.6

- v1.0.5 | Apr 05 2026:

  [Fix] _elog_json_escape() now escapes all 32 C0 control characters (0x00-0x1F)
      per RFC 8259 §7; previously missed 27 including ESC (terminal injection vector)
  [Fix] All 6 file output handlers (file, audit, syslog_file, CEF, GELF, ELK) now
      refuse to write through symlinks via _elog_safe_append() guard
  [Fix] _elog_truncate_check() refuses to truncate symlinked log files, preventing
      TOCTOU symlink-following overwrite during log rotation
  [Fix] Signal trap save/restore in truncation prevents clobbering consumer handlers;
      restores default signal disposition when no prior consumer trap was set
  [Fix] Classic format output sanitizes embedded newlines to prevent log injection
      in both elog() and elog_event() paths
  [Fix] elog_init() enforces chmod 640 on pre-existing log files, not only new files
  [New] ELOG_AUDIT_MAX_LINES: optional audit log size limit (default: 0 = disabled)
  [Change] Truncation refactored to parameterized _elog_truncate_check_file() shared
      by app log and audit log; bare cat changed to command cat
  [Change] CI: batsman 1.4.0 → 1.4.1; CI workflow pin v1.0.3 → v1.4.1
